{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/96126", "id": 911330696, "node_id": "PR_kwDOAAsO6M42Uc2I", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/96126", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/96126.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/96126.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/96126", "number": 96126, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Normalize PATH on windows to avoid unnecessary full builds", "user": {"login": "ghost", "id": 10137, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwMTM3", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10137?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost", "html_url": "https://github.com/ghost", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "I discovered that I was doing unnecessary full builds on windows due to changes in how the PATH environment variable was being presented.\r\n\r\nI saw at least 3 different versions of PATH, depending on where I was running ```x.py``` from:\r\n* VS Code\r\n* Windows Terminal\r\n* Windows Terminal launched in Quake mode\r\n\r\nIn some cases, the PATH would have duplicate entries stripped, and in other cases PATH would have a ```C:\\Program Files\\WindowsApps\\Microsoft.WindowsTerminal_1.12.10733.0_x64__8wekyb3d8bbwe``` path injected into it.\r\n\r\nThis would cause me to do full builds when switching where I was running ```x.py check``` from, even though I was making no file changes.\r\n\r\nThis PR normalizes the PATH to always have duplicate entries stripped (while retaining order), and to strip the extra path that Windows Terminal will sometimes inject. With this in place, I can run an ```x.py check``` build from all 3 locations mentioned above without doing an unnecessary full build as I switch between them.\r\n\r\nThis is a somewhat hacky \"developer machine\" oriented change... but it's in the ```x.py``` code anyway so that makes sense.", "created_at": "2022-04-16T20:04:05Z", "updated_at": "2022-04-16T23:27:32Z", "closed_at": "2022-04-16T23:27:31Z", "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "d0c1a029826a659d6c6e5b0ba4d9a510eb57f175", "assignee": {"login": "Mark-Simulacrum", "id": 5047365, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUwNDczNjU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5047365?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum", "html_url": "https://github.com/Mark-Simulacrum", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/Mark-Simulacrum/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "assignees": [{"login": "Mark-Simulacrum", "id": 5047365, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjUwNDczNjU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5047365?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "ur